# .secretlintignore — paths secretlint should NOT scan (repo-root override)
# Overrides the shared template from .mega-linter.d/.secretlintignore.
#
# Format: gitignore-style glob patterns, one per line. `**/` anchors a
# pattern at any depth. Lines starting with `#` are comments.
#
# Curation principle: only ignore content that is (a) derived, (b) known
# to produce false positives at high volume, or (c) explicitly excluded
# from linting elsewhere in this config. Do NOT add broad source-tree
# exclusions here — secretlint is most valuable when it sees as much of
# the real code as possible.

# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Dependency lockfiles
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Lockfiles contain integrity hashes and registry URLs that pattern-match
# secret-like tokens (long hex strings, base64-looking digests). They are
# generated, never source-of-truth for credentials.
**/package-lock.json
**/yarn.lock
**/pnpm-lock.yaml
**/Pipfile.lock
**/poetry.lock
**/Cargo.lock
**/go.sum
**/composer.lock

# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Linter and test outputs (derived artefacts, not source)
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# A SARIF file can contain literal "secret-looking" snippets that triggered
# OTHER scanners — running secretlint over those creates a noisy feedback
# loop. The companion .mega-linter.yml notes a prior incident where gitleaks
# generated 152 false positives from a single test SARIF for this reason.
**/megalinter-reports/**
**/.test-output/**
**/coverage/**

# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Test fixtures (canonical false-positive source)
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Test data routinely embeds fake tokens, sample JWTs, and example API keys
# to exercise parser and security paths. These are intentionally
# secret-shaped but never real credentials. Scope kept narrow — only
# fixture directories, not entire test trees, so real test code is still
# scanned.
**/testdata/**
**/test/fixtures/**
**/tests/fixtures/**
**/__fixtures__/**

# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# AI assistant directories
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# These are local-only developer configurations, never committed to track
# credentials, and already excluded from the broader linter scan via
# ADDITIONAL_EXCLUDED_DIRECTORIES in .mega-linter.yml. Mirrored here so
# secretlint stays consistent with the rest of the suite.
**/.agents/**
**/.cache/**
**/.claude/**
**/.cursor/**
**/.opencode/**
**/.specify/**
**/.uf/**

# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Repo-specific exclusions
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Generated custom MegaLinter flavor artifacts (Dockerfile, config).
**/custom-flavor/**
